<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000GMT, June 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The resignation announced
Tuesday night by Aryeh Deri from the leadership of Israel's
powerful religious Shas party has brought mixed reactions from the
country's political spectrum.
</P>
<P>
The left-wing One Israel coalition, led by Prime Minister-elect
Ehud Barak, said it will take a 24-hour break to assess the
situation before resuming the talks over forming a new government.
</P>
<P>
Israel's Center Party, Meretz, Yisrael Ba'aliya Party welcomed
Deri's decision and said it would facilitate Shas' entry into the
coalition.
</P>
<P>
Israel's secular party Shinui insisted however it would not
join the new government if Shas entered the coalition, with or
without Deri as its leader. (BC-Israel-Shas)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli President Ezer Weizman Wednesday expressed
welcome to Shas party leader Aryeh Deri's decision to resign from
the party's leadership.
</P>
<P>
Deri announced his resignation Tuesday night at Shas party
headquarters in Jerusalem. (BC-Israel-Deri-Reaction)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The spiritual leaders of Israel's powerful
religious Shas party Wednesday accepted the resignation of the
party's political leader Aryeh Deri, a move which would facilitate
Shas's entry into the new government.
</P>
<P>
After a two-hour meeting in Jerusalem, Shas's Council of Torah
Sages, led by the party's spiritual leader Rabbi Ovadia Yosef,
announced that it accepted Deri's resignation with great regret.
(BC-Israel-Shas)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish Foreign Ministry Deputy Spokesman Sermet
Atacanli said here Wednesday that Turkey disapproves of the G-8
countries' initiative regarding the Cyprus issue.
</P>
<P>
Atacanli told reporters that the initiative constituted an
interference in the United Nations goodwill mission on the
long-divided island.
</P>
<P>
He was referring to a June 10 statement by the group's foreign
ministers, which calls for an immediate resumption of the dialog
between the two Cypriot sides with no preconditions, and their
upcoming summit in Cologne, where the Cyprus issue will be again
on the agenda. (BC-Turkey-G-8-Cyprus) 
</P>
</TEXT>
