<HEADLINE> Turkey to Buy Helicopters to Fight Forest Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Turkey is planning to buy 14
helicopters through international bidding to fight forest fires
in the country.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Forestry Director Ahmet Ulukanligil said that in 1997, a
project, entitled "Fighting Forest Fires," was initiated so that
the necessary vehicles and equipment could be acquired through
foreign loans to fight forest blaze from land and air, Anatolian
News Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Ulukanligil said that their use of the latest fire fighting
techniques will include the necessary acquisition of a tanker
truck that jettisons a spray of water from its tank, a trailer
used for transport, a bulldozer, wireless phones and helicopters.
</P>
<P>
"With the acquisition of all this, the forestry organization
will guarantee its supplies for the next 20-25 years," he
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
