<HEADLINE> Nigerian House Speaker Emphasizes Ties With China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABUJA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Alhaji Buhari, Speaker of Nigeria's
House of the Representatives Wednesday cited Chinese involvement
in the country's railway rehabilitation as a living evidence of
good cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We hope to form a strong base for cordial relationship between
China and Nigeria," Buhari told Chinese Ambassador Liang Yinzhu,
who presented a congratulation letter by Li Peng, Chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress of China.
</P>
<P>
"Both countries enjoyed excellent diplomatic relations since
the 1979s," said Li in the letter.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the friendship and cooperation
between the two countries and the two countries' legislatures
will be further expended.
</P>
<P>
Buhari, while thanking Liang for visiting him as the first
foreign ambassador, pledged that Nigeria will continue to adhere
to the one-China policy.
</P>
<P>
Buhari was elected and sworn in as the head of the House of
Representative, or lower chamber of Nigeria's legislature, on a
June 3 inauguration session. 
</P>
