<HEADLINE> France Closes Strategic Nuclear Missile Base </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- France closed on Wednesday its
strategic nuclear missile base on the Plateau of Albion in the
southeast part of the country, which served as one of France's
nuclear deterrence bases from 1971 till 1996, Agence France-Presse
quoted military sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The 800 sq-km large base, called Base 200, came into operation
in 1971 with ground-to-ground middle range strategic nuclear
missiles officially targeted at the former Soviet Union.
</P>
<P>
The nuclear missiles were dismantled on September 16, 1996, and
all the nuclear materials were removed from the base last year.
</P>
<P>
The work of completely closing the base, including the
re-settlement of the thousands of civil and military personnel at
the base, has more than three years.
</P>
<P>
The base will be taken over in August by an engineers' regiment
of the Foreign Legion and the counter-espionage agency Direction
Generale de la Securite Exterieure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
