<HEADLINE> Iran Backs Lebanese Resistance Against Israel: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi said Wednesday that his forthcoming visit to Lebanon is
aimed at supporting the Lebanese resistance against Israel.
</P>
<P>
Iran supports those who resist Israel's expansionist policies,
Kharrazi said on the eve of his five-day visit to Lebanon and
Jordan, the Islamic Republic News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Terming Lebanon as a country on the forefront of struggle
against Israel, he said the resistance of the Lebanese people
against Israel is a source of pride for Muslims and has brought
unity and solidarity among various Lebanese ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a self-declared security zone in south Lebanon in
1985 with a claimed aim of protecting its north from Lebanese
guerrillas' cross-border attacks.
</P>
<P>
Iranian-back Hezbollah, or Party of God, has since been
spearheading a guerrilla war to oust the Israeli occupation troops
and their allied South Lebanon Army out of the country.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian minister stressed that the Middle East region is
one of the sensitive areas in the world, to which Iran's foreign
policy gives top priority.
</P>
<P>
On his visit to Jordan, Kharrazi said that his trip is
regarded as a reciprocal response to a recent visit to Iran by
the Jordanian foreign minister.
</P>
<P>
He said that his talks with Jordanian officials will cover
bilateral ties and other matters of mutual interests.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the visit will lead to further
promotion and consolidation of Iran-Jordan relations. 
</P>
