<HEADLINE> Tanzanian Mayor Attacked by Bandits in Bar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Eight bandits attacked the
mayor of Arusha in north Tanzanian Tuesday evening at a bar and
made away with a pistol, 10 rounds of ammunition and some money,
Xinhua learned here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The bandits hit and hurt Arusha Municipality Mayor Philiph
Kivuyo with bottles when he was staying with two colleagues in a
local bar at midnight, said Inspector General of Police's Press
Secretary Mohamed Mhina.
</P>
<P>
Mhina also said the bandits robbed 50,000 shillings (about 70
U.S. dollars) from the mayor and injured him in the Big Sisters
Bar at Kigenge area.
</P>
<P>
The incident was confirmed Wednesday by the Arusha Regional
Commissioner, Daniel ole Njoolay. In a telephone interview with
Xinhua, he said the police are still hunting for the gang.
</P>
<P>
The mayor, who was wounded in the face and leg, has been
hospitalized but is in stable condition, Njoolay said from the
central city of Dodoma.
</P>
<P>
Police in Arusha said the bandits also grabbed 100,000
shillings from the bar owner and 30,000 shillings from one of the
mayor's colleagues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
