<HEADLINE> More Than 50,000 Gather for Inauguration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRETORIA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- A crowd of more than 50,000
people had gathered on Pretoria's Union Building lawns by mid-day
on Wednesday to commemorate the inauguration of Thabo Mbeki as
South Africa's second democratic president.
</P>
<P>
The inauguration proceedings at the Union Buildings were shown
to the crowd on a giant screen, and they roared their approval at
the events.
</P>
<P>
The biggest cheers were reserved for outgoing president Nelson
Mandela, but Mbeki also got his fair share of applause.
</P>
<P>
Many of those in the crowd wore T-shirts especially printed for
the event and handed out to those who braved the chilly morning
air and arrived early.
</P>
<P>
The focus of the day's proceedings are to move from the Union
Buildings in Pretoria down to the gardens Wednesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Mbeki and Mandela are due to address the crowd, which will then
be treated to an eight-hour concert.
</P>
<P>
People danced and sang throughout the morning enjoying the
perfect weather and police said no incidents had been reported.
</P>
