the Public Service Association and Zimbabwe Nurses Association
held a press conference Tuesday on the issue.
</P>
<P>
ZIMTA President Leonard Nkala said the decision to call off the
national strike would depend on the government's commitment to
negotiate.
</P>
<P>
"We are allowing the negotiations of the 20 percent between now
 and Friday so that the issue can be presented to the next cabinet
meeting," he said. 
</P>
