<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Islamic Countries Agree to Form Parliamentary Union </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Lawmakers of member states of the
Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC) agreed Wednesday to
establish the Parliamentary Union of the OIC.
</P>
<P>
The decision was made after a charter was passed in the
founding conference of the union, which was previously named as
the Organization of the Islamic Parliaments.
</P>
<P>
According to the charter, the union will comprise legislative,
consultative assemblies or similar bodies (parliaments) of the
OIC member states.
</P>
<P>
The union was intended to enhance cooperation and coordination
among the OIC parliaments and between these parliaments and
parliamentary, governmental and non-governmental organizations of
other countries.
</P>
<P>
It also aims to foster coordination among peoples of the world
in order to respect and defend human rights and humanitarian
principles and establishment of peace, based on justice.
</P>
<P>
According to the charter, the union will have four organs of
conference, the council, the executive committee and the
secretariat.
</P>
<P>
The conference consists of speakers of member parliaments of
the union or their representatives, in addition to a maximum of
four parliamentarians from each member of the union.
</P>
<P>
The conference will convene once every two years and the
council, comprising two lawmakers of each member state, will
convene once a year with the presence of more than half of its
members.
</P>
<P>
The three-day founding conference started Tuesday with
participation of about 40 Islamic countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
