<HEADLINE> Guangdong Makes Progress In Fighting Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 16 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangdong Province
has uncovered a total of 9,248 smuggling cases, with a total
value of 5.227 billion yuan (630 million U.S. dollars) in the last
twelve months or so.
</P>
<P>
The vice-governor in charge of the anti-smuggling campaign,
Tang Bingquan, said that the smuggled goods included cars, refined
oil, edible oil, textile products, raw materials for the chemical
industry and cigarettes.
</P>
<P>
The number of suspects involved in smuggling for the whole
province reached 449, among which 221 have already been sentenced.
</P>
