<HEADLINE> U.N. Agencies Warn of Malnutrition in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of thousands of
Angolans face an increased risk of malnutrition, according to a
new report issued here by the U.N. Food and Agriculture
Organization (FAO) and the World Food Program (WFP) on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Escalating violence in Angola is severely disrupting
agriculture, with a number of farming areas engulfed by fighting,
said the agencies.
</P>
<P>
Some 1.7 million displaced people are virtually isolated because
of the ongoing fighting.
</P>
<P>
Less than one third of the needed aid has been pledged by
donors, and the agencies said without this support, food shortages
would only worsen in the coming months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
