<HEADLINE> Flag-Passing Activity Marks Protection of Chinese Rivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Two flags bearing the words of "
Action to Protect the Mother Rivers" will start as of today being
passed down from the upper reaches of the Yangtze and Yellow
rivers.
</P>
<P>
The event, participated by college and high school students, is
aimed to arouse the conscience of the nation to protect the
environment of China's two longest rivers, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
A flag-awarding ceremony was held today in northwest China's
Qinghai Province, the source of the two rivers, with more than 100
well-known people signing their names on the flags.
</P>
<P>
The Yellow River's flag will reach Dongying City in east China'
s Shandong Province, via 24 cities; and the Yangtze River's flag
will pass through 32 cities until it is given to Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The activity will end in September. Delegates of Dongying and
Shanghai cities will gather in Beijing with the flags for a
closing ceremony on September 4, organizers said.
</P>
<P>
The event was sponsored by the Central Committee of the
Communist Youth League of China and a number of ministries.
</P>
