<HEADLINE> China's Stock Turnover Hits New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Composite Stock Index for the Shanghai exchange closed the
session at 1,501.1 points, the highest level since May 1997. The B-
share index, which indicates the performance of shares reserved
for overseas investors, rose 2.8 percent on Wednesday's level to
end at 49.36 points. Total transaction for the day reached a
record 29.42 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Some 354 of the 498 stocks listed on the Shanghai bourse were
up, including 47 stocks which closed at the daily growth limit.
Some 130 stocks closed down for the day.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen Component Stock Index closed the session at 3,883.
60 points, up 2.98 percent on Wednesday, with the B-share index
ended up 2.95 percent. Turnover in the Shenzhen exchange hit 21.
427 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Policy factors are expected to fuel the continuing upward
movement of the stock market in coming days, according to market
analysts. However, they also note the likelihood of corrections.
</P>
