<HEADLINE> Man. United to Play Shanghai Shenhua at Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Triple champions Manchester
United will open its Asia tour with a friendly against Chinese top
club Shanghai Shenhua on July 21.
</P>
<P>
Man. United, which has just completed an unprecedented sweep of
the league, F.A. Cup and European Cup in the same season, hailed
the Asia tour as an important part in their build-up to next
season.
</P>
<P>
"Shanghai Shenhua is an excellent club. We will treat the
friendly as important as winning the league, F.A. cup and European
Cup," United senior official Peter Kenyon said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Shenhua, the only club who grabbed both titles of the Chinese
league and F.A. in one season, also greeted the match as "a very
meaningful event".
</P>
<P>
"Man. United is one of the greatest teams in the world. We
believe there will be a sell-out crowd in the 80,000-seat Shanghai
Stadium," said Shenhua president Yu Zhifei.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United made no secret of their strong interest in
entering the lucrative Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
"China football has a great market. We hope more Chinese
players go to play in England, and we are ready to co-operate with
China in more fields," Kenyon said.
</P>
<P>
Kenyon was referring to Fan Zhiyi of Shenhua and Sun Jihai of
reigning league champions Dalian Wanda who have played in the
English first division club Crystal Palace in the 1998-99 season.
</P>
<P>
"We have been looking at what happens to Asia soccer and keep a
close eye on the development of Chinese football," Kenyon said.
</P>
<P>
Manchester will begin their training session on July 5 to
prepare for the Asia tour which also includes a match with the
Hong Kong club side of South China on July 24, the last of United'
s warm-up matches for the next season.
</P>
<P>
The tickets for the Shanghai match had been sold out five weeks
in advance, which is the first time ever for the Shanghai Stadium.
</P>
</TEXT>
