<HEADLINE> Shanghai Exchange Lists Bonds for Three Gorges Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Two billion yuan in construction
bonds for the Three Gorges Project in the middle reaches of the
Yangtze River were listed today on the Shanghai Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The bonds, issued between January 18 and February 6 this year,
represented the second group of bonds issued especially for the
mammoth Three Gorges Project. Funds raised through the bond issue
will be used to finance construction of the project during 1999.
</P>
<P>
The issue includes one billion yuan in 3-year bonds which a
single annual interest rate of 5.6 percent and additional one
billion yuan in 8-year bonds with an annual interest rate of 6.2
percent.
</P>
<P>
The bonds were issued at par value and carry a triple-A rating,
the highest rating for corporate bonds, granted by the China
Chengxin Appraisal Co. Limited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
