<HEADLINE> Netherlands vs. Australia in Champions Trophy Women's Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 17 (Xinhua -- The Netherlands secured the point
necessary for a berth in the final as they held the world and
Olympic champions Australia to a 1-1 draw on Thursday in the
Champions Trophy women's hockey tournament at Brisbane, Australia.
</P>
<P>
With Australia already in the final following a 4-0 record in
the six-nation tournament, the Netherlands capitalized on a rare
defensive error to go ahead 1-0 through Fleur van de Kieft in the
20th minute.
</P>
<P>
Australian striker Alyson Annan canceled out the lead four
minutes later but neither side was able to find the net until the
match faded out to a draw.
</P>
<P>
The tie killed the last hopes of Germany who would have gone
through if the Dutch had slipped up against the Australians after
winning 4-0 over South Korea earlier in the day.
</P>
<P>
Germany opened their account after just five minutes when
Franziska Gude scored but the team failed to find the net again in
the first half.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans, who were yet to win in the round-robin
matches, hung on desperately only to see the dominating Germans
add three more goals through Britta Becka, Heike Latzsch and
Natascha Keller.
</P>
<P>
The Germans will now face Argentina in Saturday's bronze medal
play-off after the South Americans drew 2-2 with New Zealand. The
New Zealanders will play South Korea in the play-off for fifth
spot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
