<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Breakthrough in SOEs Reform (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The restructuring of China's state-
owned enterprises (SOEs) has reached a crucial stage and efforts
should be intensified in solving the outstanding problems now
facing them, Chinese President Jiang Zemin said today.
</P>
<P>
"We must fully realize the importance and urgency in solving
these problems as they are crucial to completing the reform of
the SOEs reform and shaking off the poverty with three years,"
Jiang said at a forum on the topic in Xi'an, which was attended by
provincial officials from five northwestern China provinces and
autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
"The causes of the problems are various, but the only way out
for SOEs is to deepen the current reform and turn enterprises into
market-oriented ones," Jiang stressed.
</P>
<P>
Concrete measures should be taken to improve the management of
SOEs and establish a strict responsibility system to ensure the
stable increase in the value of state-owned assets.
</P>
<P>
"To better restructure SOEs, China should strive to develop its
high-tech industry and phase out old fashioned industries.
Meanwhile, it is also important to rejuvenate small- and medium-
sized enterprises," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Further efforts should be taken to readjust and improve the
structure of the state sector to create a situation in which
public ownership serves as the backbone while other forms of
ownership enjoy smooth development," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Jiang promised that the government will adopt active measures
within its financial capability to gradually help SOEs solve such
problems as shortage of capital, high debt ratio and heavy social
burdens.
</P>
<P>
"The reassignment of laid-off workers is directly related to
the overall situation of reform, development and stability," he
said. "All localities and government departments must strictly
implement the series of principles and policies that the central
government has made to ensure all laid-off workers are properly
settled."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
