<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Breakthrough In SOEs Reform (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang urged all local leading officials to be audacious and
innovative in tackling prominent problems in the course of
reforming and developing the SOEs.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has a large population with but a
comparatively weak economy and underdeveloped productive forces,
and this determines that it will take a long period of time to
solve the prominent problems.
</P>
<P>
Jiang urged all the local officials to lead the people to
surmount the difficulties and sum up fresh experience and tackle
the problems by every means.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese leader stressed that Northwest China is home to
many minority ethnic groups and that it is extremely important to
strengthen their unity and maintain political and social stability.
</P>
<P>
Maintaining political and social stability is "the common
aspiration" of China's 56 nationalities and accords with their
fundamental interests, he said, pointing out that this has a vital
bearing on the country's reform, opening up and socialist
modernization drive as a whole.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that the people of the country's 56 nationalities
are pressing ahead along the road of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics and this excellent situation is "hard-won".
Local leading officials should lead them to continue to push ahead
the cause of reform, opening up and the socialist modernization
drive, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
