<HEADLINE> Danube Traffic to Be Resumed by End-1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Traffic on the River Danube,
paralyzed after NATO warplanes sank several bridges in their
bombardment of Yugoslavia, will resume by the end of this year,
the official Rompres news agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted Romanian Transport Minister Traian Basescu as
saying certain restrictions were expected in places in the first
phase of reopening the traffic.
</P>
<P>
