would be included in the top priorities of the reconstruction
program in the Balkans.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, the European Union is ready to
allocate 1.3 billion euro (about 1.2 billion U.S. dollars) to tow
the twisted ironworks out of the waters and set the waterway free.
</P>
<P>
Romanian shipping operators are faced with a weekly loss of 11
million dollars after traffic on Danube was put to a halt in the
aftermath of the NATO bombing campaign in Yugoslavia. 
