<HEADLINE> Roundup: In Search of a Peaceful Environment (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Wannian, vice-chairman of
China's Central Military Commission (CMC), concluded his visit to
China's northern neighbor Russia and returned here today.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, both sides reached extensive consensus amid a
friendly and cordial atmosphere, which represents the latest
development in China's busy military exchanges with neighboring
countries.
</P>
<P>
Almost all of China's senior military leaders chose nearby
countries as destinations for their visits this year. No sooner
had the traditional Spring Festival was over than Chinese Defense
Minister Chi Haotian flew to Pakistan, and Fu Quanyou, chief of
the General Staff of Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA),
visited Malaysia and Australia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, China welcomed military leaders from over ten
neighbors, including defense ministers from Cambodia, Thailand,
Laos, Australia and the Minister of the People's Armed Forces of
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), as well as army
leaders from Bangladesh, Pakistan, Mongolia, amongst others. An
even larger number of specific exchanges and cooperation meetings
at lower levels have also taken place.
