<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: In Search of a Peaceful Environment (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In another development, along with the arrival of the first
senior state delegation of the Democratic People's Republic of
Korea (DPRK) since 1994, the year its then leader Kim Il Sung
passed away, the two armies of China and DPRK, which have enjoyed
a traditional friendship stretching back decades, had their first
high-level meeting in five years.
</P>
<P>
Undoubtedly, this event was of positive significance toward
implementing lasting peace and stability on the Korean Peninsula
and even the whole of northeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
While the issues of the Korean Peninsula and south Asia are
regional in their characteristics, the meeting between the
military leaders of China and Russia not only concern peace in the
Asia-Pacific region, but exerts a far reaching impact on world
peace and stability in general.
</P>
<P>
During a ten-day visit, Zhang Wannian met with members of the
Russian government and army leaders and exchanged views on
regional and international security, and other issues of common
concern.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990617.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: In Search of a Peaceful Environment (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
There have been more military delegations from neighboring
countries than from other regions and the number of senior
delegations headed by defense ministers or army leaders is greater
than that in the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Therefore comprehensive and active relationships with
surrounding areas have become a major feature of China's military
diplomacy this year.
</P>
<P>
Despite the fact that Asia remains a relatively stable area as
is known to all, there are still elements that threaten regional
peace. Given that situation, China, as a significant player in
regional and international affairs, has used its influence to urge
those involved countries to avoid crisis situations through
dialogue in an effort to secure a peaceful all-round environment.
</P>
<P>
The visit by the Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Pakistani
Staff Committee to China aroused considerable attention. Chinese
President and CMC Chairman Jiang Zemin met with him and said that
"the peace and prosperity of the entire Asia would not be possible
without the stability and development of south Asia". Other
Chinese army leaders repeatedly expressed their hopes that "
relevant parties continue their patient and candid dialogues in a
bid to resolve differences and problems".
</P>
</TEXT>
