<DOCNO> XIE19990617.0136 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Sharemarket Closes Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Australian sharemarket closed
higher Thursday in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark all ordinaries index closed 38.1 points, or 1.29
per cent, higher at 2980.3.
</P>
<P>
The all industrials index was even stronger adding 79.6 points,
or 1.55 per cent, to 5213 points while the all resources index
added just 0.2 of a point to 1208.8 points.
</P>
<P>
As fears of an imminent interest rate rise in the United States
eased a rush of buying on the Australian market in local bank
stocks was inspired.
</P>
<P>
Industrial stocks and in particular bank shares were further
boosted when Reserve Bank of Australia governor Ian Macfarlane
confirmed that there was no prima facie case for a change to
interest rates here.
</P>
<P>
The banking index soared 2.80 per cent, with National Australia
Bank jumping more than three per cent or 83.1 cents to 25.771
Australian dollars. the Commonwealth bank gained almost four per
cent, adding 91 cents to 24.95 Australian dollars, Westpac bank
added 18.5 cents to 9.945 Australian dollars and ANZ bank lifted
35.6 cents to 10.97 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among resource stocks, mining giant Rio Tinto slipped 31.4
cents to 24.018 Australian dollars, while rival BHP gained 40.6
cents to 17.706 Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 435.05 million shares traded worth 850.2
million U.S. dollars with 672 shares rising, 612 falling and 459
remaining steady. 
</P>
</TEXT>
