<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EBank Completes Merger with China Investment Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The China Everbright Bank (EBank)
announced here today that it has successfully taken over the
assets, liabilities, equity and 10 business institutions of the
Shanghai branch of the former China Investment Bank (CIB).
</P>
<P>
This means that the EBank has now completed the take-over of
the CIB by acquiring assets, liabilities, equity and 137 banking
offices countrywide.
</P>
<P>
The restructuring brings EBank's assets to 150 billion yuan and
the number of its business institutions to 245, making it the 6th
largest commercial bank in China.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1992, the EBank is China's first foreign share-
holding commercial bank, whose major share holders include the
China Everbright Group Ltd and the Asian Development Bank
</P>
<P>
Set up in 1994, EBank Shanghai branch gives priority to
supporting local foreign trade, hi-tech enterprises and excellent
enterprises in other fields. 
</P>
</TEXT>
