<HEADLINE> Zanzibar to Hold International Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 17 (Xinhua) -- An international trade fair
will be held in Zanzibar to give local small-scale traders an
international exposure and restore the lost glory of the isles as
a mercantile center in east and central Africa.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair will take place from October 29 to November 7 at
the House of Wonders situated in the heart of the well-known Stone
Town, media reports said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Several reputable companies from African countries, the Gulf
region and European nations have shown interest in the event,
Nassor Mazrui, chairman of the Zanzibar Chamber of Commerce,
Industries and Agriculture, said in Zanzibar Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The fair is jointly organized by the chamber, and the Women
Development for All, an non-governmental organization (NGO) led by
Salma Salmin Amour, wife of Zanzibar President.
</P>
<P>
The fair will provide a chance for women to prove their ability
in entrepreneurship, she said.
</P>
<P>
Mazuri said foreign exhibitors will be allowed to bring their
products into Zanzibar exempted from all duties.
</P>
<P>
Zanzibar, part of the United Republic of Tanzania, was a
booming trading center of slaves and cloves in history. Economy
in the isles has worsened due to suspension of foreign aid.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, an international trade fair will be held in the
Tanzanian capital Dar es Salaam during July 2-10, according to the
Board of External Trade (BET), the organizer.
</P>
<P>
So far, businessmen from 28 foreign countries have confirmed
participation in the annual event, which is to take place on the
Saba Saba grounds in the capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
