<HEADLINE> South African Company to Participate in Angola's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's major oil company,
Energy Africa, has said it will participate more in Angola's oil
exploitation through attending public bidding for offshore
tapping.
</P>
<P>
The decision was revealed by John Bentley, general manager of
Energy Africa, during his visit here in Angola, The Angola Daily
