<HEADLINE> Interest Subsidies Could Boost Industrial Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- In a bid to maintain the strong
momentum in China's economic growth, the country's financial
institutions may offer loans with interest repayments reduced
through a government backed subsidy to encourage investment in the
industrial sector, a boost to fixed assets.
</P>
<P>
This has been revealed by Chen Huai, a researcher from the
Market Economy Research Institute under the State Council's
Research Center for Development.
</P>
<P>
Chen said in a report published in yesterday's China Economic
Times that new fiscal policy aimed at stimulating domestic demand
may help boost economic growth under the current economic
situation.
</P>
<P>
Presently, the growth of fixed asset investment has slowed down
while the savings of citizens have been increasing at a high speed.
A growth of investment made by the public will be of great help to
China's pro-active fiscal policies in expanding domestic demand,
according to Chen.
</P>
<P>
Chen elaborated in his report that a large scale boosting of
fixed assets and the technical upgrading will solve the problem of
the slowing economic growth by sharpening the competitive edge of
industrial manufacturers as well as tapping the potential of idle
resources.
</P>
<P>
In view of this, the government may provide subsidies on the
interest of loans to encourage public investment. Chen believes
that a three-year-long program linked to interest subsidies may
enable the whole industrial sector to be upgraded, including steel,
automobiles, machinery and textiles, reaching an advanced level in
the world.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the new initiative may contribute to the development
of a sound capital market in China, according to the report.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
