<HEADLINE> OIC Parliamentary Union Founding Conference Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The founding conference of the
Parliamentary Union of the Organization of Islamic Conference
(OIC) Members concluded here Thursday morning.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman of the conference Taha Hashemi said at a press
conference that the union's council would open its first session
Thursday afternoon to elect its secretary general.
</P>
<P>
Hashemi said the union has decided to base its permanent
secretariat in Tehran, the first time for Iran to host the
secretariat of an international organization since the Islamic
Revolution in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from 49 Islamic countries, including 28
parliament speakers, attended the three-day founding conference
and all the participating countries were named as the union's
founding members, he said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the change in the name of the body, which was
originally "the Organization of Islamic Parliament," Hashemi said
the name was changed to "the Parliamentary Union of the OIC
Members" because some OIC members are not Islamic countries while
some others have secular parliaments.
</P>
<P>
Asked about the relations between the union and the OIC,
Hashemi said the newly-established union is an independent
organization.
</P>
<P>
"It has no contradiction with the OIC and it is not a
subordinate to the OIC, but an independent organization," he
said, adding the union would have close cooperation and
coordination with the OIC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
