<HEADLINE> China, Bulgaria Seek Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Chinese enterprises have been
invited to invest in infrastructure building projects in Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
The request came from visiting Bulgarian Foreign Minister
Nadezhda Mikhailova here today who made the remarks at a Sino-
Bulgarian commercial seminar.
</P>
<P>
"Good trade relation buttresses bilateral relations," she said,
pointing out that there is great trade potential between the two
sides and called for the re-opening of the ancient Silk Road
linking China and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Peter Denev, who led the Bulgarian business delegation, mostly
comprised of representatives from the construction and light
industry sectors, said they were attracted by the fast development
of the Chinese economy.
</P>
<P>
"Bulgaria has already imported many light industrial products,
household appliances and domestic mechanized equipment from China
and hopes to establish joint ventures with Chinese enterprises to
make these kinds of products by using factories and technologies
in Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
Yu Xiaosong, President of the China Council for the Promotion
of International Trade, which hosted the trade seminar, was also
present at the event.
</P>
<P>
He briefed the visitors on China's economic development and
bilateral trade, and encouraged more communication between the two
sides. 
</P>
</TEXT>
