<HEADLINE> SAFE Makes Serious Efforts to Provide Good Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- China's State Administration of
Foreign Exchange (SAFE) has made great efforts this year to
improve the administration of foreign exchange and offer high
quality services.
</P>
<P>
An official from the SAFE said that by the end of March, China'
s foreign exchange reserves had reached 146.62 billion U.S.
dollars, an increase of 1.666 billion U.S. dollars over the end of
last year, with the foreign exchange market operation basically
normal.
</P>
<P>
When the SAFE held its annual meeting at the beginning of this
year, it clearly outlined its work targets which included
maintaining balanced international payments and a stable currency,
creating a good environment for foreign trade and foreign
investment, and promoting the healthy development of the foreign
economic activities.
</P>
<P>
To offer higher quality services and improve the operating
efficiency of enterprises and banks, the SAFE launched a new check
clearing computer system on January 1 among customs offices, banks
and the SAFE itself, reducing time spent on clearing and
administering checks from two or three weeks to a few minutes.
</P>
<P>
The SAFE has also created a fair, open, healthy and clean legal
environment for foreign exchange administration by drafting a
series of foreign exchange policies, which has enabled it to offer
high quality foreign exchange services.
</P>
<P>
"The recent launch of the SAFE website is one of the measures
taken to increase its openness and improve communications with the
community," the official said, adding that foreign investors
attending a recent seminar held by the SAFE have expressed their
appreciation for the good competitive environment created by
foreign exchange administrative departments.  
</P>
</TEXT>
