<HEADLINE> Chinese, Bulgarian Foreign Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan and his Bulgarian counterpart Nadezhda Mikhailova held
talks here today, and signed two agreements for cooperation in the
fields of education and social affairs respectively.
</P>
<P>
It has been 50 years since China and Bulgaria forged diplomatic
ties, and through the joint efforts of both sides, bilateral ties
have witnessed further development in recent years, Tang said.
</P>
<P>
He expressed appreciation for the principled position of the
Bulgarian government to actively develop relations with China and
pursue the "one China" policy on the issue of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
He also voiced the hope that Bulgaria would continue to keep
alert against the "diplomatic breakthrough" sought by the Taiwan
authorities in any form and under any name with the aim of
destroying the China-Bulgaria friendship.
</P>
<P>
Mikhailova spoke highly of bilateral ties, saying political
relations have been sound, and that there is great potential for
the expansion of economic and trade cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Bulgaria is willing to continue reinforcing its cooperation
with China in various fields, she said, stressing Bulgaria will
not change its consistent stance on the Taiwan issue, let alone
conduct political contact with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers also discussed international issues
of common concern including the Kosovo issue and cooperation in
specific fields, especially in the economic and trade sector.
</P>
</TEXT>
