<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai-Fukushima Air Route Launched </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A new non-stop air service
linking Shanghai, China's economic center, with Japan's Fukushima
was launched today by China Eastern Airlines.
</P>
<P>
A 146-seat B737 aircraft, which was to inaugurate the service
was replaced by a 276-seat A 300 airbus due to the larger number
of passengers than expected for the virgin flight.
</P>
<P>
The flight is 1,988 kilometers long and will take three hours
to arrive at Fukushima, which is located nearly 200 km northeast
of Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
This is the seventh air route the airline flies to Japan and
also the 23rd international route it operates.
</P>
<P>
The service will offer two flights a week, on Thursdays and
Sundays.  
</P>
</TEXT>
