<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Sharply Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 253.15
points, or 1.92 percent, to close at 13,408.27 Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market was buoyed by a flat U.S. inflation
number that eased fears that the U.S. Federal Reserve planned
several interest rate rises in coming months.
</P>
<P>
Shares for finance, utilities, properties and commerce and
industry increased 1.69 percent, 3.09 percent, 1.57 percent and 1.
35 percent respectively after Wednesday's sharp gains.
</P>
<P>
China-related shares also increased sharply with the Hang Seng
China Enterprises Index going up 2.97 percent and the Hang Seng
China-Affiliated Corporations Index up 2.92 percent.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's market turnover was 8.403 billion HK dollars (about
1.077 billion U.S. dollars), 2.157 billion HK dollars (about 276
million U.S. dollars) more than Wednesday's 6.246 billion HK
dollars (about 801 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The stock market Thursday opened higher with the key Hang Seng
Index gaining 215.34 points, or 1.64 percent, at 13,370.46.
</P>
<P>
The HSI increased 215.21 points, or 1.64 percent, to close the
morning session at 13,370.33.  
</P>
</TEXT>
