<HEADLINE> China to Enhance Science Cooperation With Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese official said here on
Thursday that China and Portugal have promising potentials in
scientific and technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Being one member of the European Union, Portugal can play a
bigger role in pushing forward scientific and technological
cooperation between China and European countries," said Jin
Zhonghua, an official with China's Ministry of Science and
Technology.
</P>
<P>
Jin made the remarks at the opening ceremony of a two-day
International Forum on Scientific and Technological Culture in
Europe and Asia held in Macao.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Europe has been China's important cooperative
partner, and the two can make use of each other's advantages for
mutual development.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and technological cooperation between China and
Portugal has been well under way since 1993 when the two
governments signed an agreement in this regard.
</P>
<P>
In March 1998, ministers in charge of science and technology
from the two countries signed a joint statement which laid a solid
foundation for further Sino-Portuguese cooperation.
</P>
<P>
In May this year, science officials of the two countries met in
Beijing and fixed on 19 cooperative projects covering agriculture,
biology, information, telecommunications, new materials and
environment.
</P>
<P>
"The field of Sino-Portuguese scientific and technological
cooperation is expanding and the cooperation is very promising,"
Jin said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
