<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Urban Services Department Saves 1.3 Bln HK Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Urban Services
Department saved 1.3 billion HK dollars (about 167 million U.S.
dollars) in the past two years as a result of its cost-saving
efforts, according to a government press release here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Elaine Chung Lai Kwok, director of Urban Services, said
Thursday that the savings were mainly achieved by streamlining
procedures, cutting operational costs and reviewing staffing
requirements.
</P>
<P>
The department achieved significant savings of eight percent in
1997-1998, 11 percent in 1998-1999, and plans to save another 11
percent or 810 million HK dollars (about 103 million U.S. dollars)
in 1999-2000.
</P>
<P>
Since 1997, the department has launched cost-saving initiatives
to enhance productivity and to optimize the use of resources.
</P>
</TEXT>
