<HEADLINE> Thailand's CP Group to Double Frozen Food Output </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 17 (Xinhua) -- CP Retailing &AMP; Marketing Ltd., a
subsidiary of Thailand's agro-industry giant Charoen Pokphand
Group, will invest 70 million baht (1.9 million U.S. dollars) to
double the size of its frozen food production, a CP report
available here Thursday said.
</P>
<P>
The expansion is part of the firm's strategy to boost its
output to 800 tons a month from the current 400 tons.
</P>
<P>
Sales are targeted at 600 million baht (16.2 million dollars)
this year, a 20 percent increase from 500 million baht (13.5
million dollars) reported last year.
</P>
<P>
Certain products, dim sum and bakery lines, will also be
exported to Australia, Canada, New Zealand and the United States,
and distributed among airlines, supermarkets and leading
restaurants.
</P>
<P>
Of the 70-million-baht planned investment, 60 million baht
(1.62 million dollars) will be used to increase the production
capacity and the variety of frozen food products.
</P>
<P>
The remaining 10 million baht (270,270 dollars) is earmarked
for bakery production at its existing plants.
</P>
<P>
CP Retailing &AMP; Marketing was awarded the ISO 14001 and ISO 9002
certificates for its dim sum plant Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
