<HEADLINE> New Acting Mayor Appointed for Southwest Municipality </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The 17th session of the First
People's Congress Standing Committee of the Chongqing Municipality
in southwest China has decided to appoint Bao Xuding as the deputy
and acting mayor of the municipality to replace former mayor Pu
Haiqing who has resigned after two years in office.
</P>
<P>
Born in 1939, Bao Xuding is a native of Wuxi City in east China
's Jiangsu Province. He was appointed as a Standing Committee
member and deputy secretary of the Communist Party of China (CPC)
Chongqing Municipal Committee this month. He is also a member of
the 15th CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Bao graduated from the Shenyang School of Mechanical Industry
in 1958 and joined the CPC in 1961. He served as deputy director
and director of the Sichuan Provincial Department of Machine
Building Industry and director of the Sichuan Provincial Economic
Planning Commission.
</P>
<P>
He served as vice-minister of machinery and electronics
industry between 1990 and 1993; vice-minister of machine building
industry between 1993 and 1996 and minister of machine building
industry between 1996 and 1998.
</P>
<P>
Bao was appointed vice-minister of state development planning
Commission in 1998.  
