<HEADLINE> Zambia Arrests 10 Congo (K) Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has arrested ten rebels of
the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) in Kaputa, north of Zambia,
on suspicion that they were part of the group of 67 which raided
Lambe Chomba in Kaputa District early this month.
</P>
<P>
The Post newspaper Thursday quoted an officer at Kaputa police
as saying Wednesday that the gunmen were arrested Tuesday after a
heavy exchange of fire.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen, belonging to the rebel movement determined to
topple DRC President Laurent Kabila, were disarmed and brought to
the police station.
</P>
<P>
Other members of the group ran towards Chinteteba on the banks
of Chomba stream where a heavy exchange of gun fire continued
throughout Tuesday, said the police officer.
</P>
<P>
A Zambia National Service soldier was shot dead in the raid on
June 1. Two civilians were also shot in the exchange of fire.
</P>
<P>
About 30,000 refugees have fled to the northern part of Zambia
from the DRC since the war broke out in the east part of the vast
central African country 10 months ago. 
</P>
