<HEADLINE> Rescue Group Rushes to Flooded Qinghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- An emergency rescue squad has
rushed to Zeku County in the Huangnan Tibet Autonomous Prefecture,
the area most severely hit by floods in northwest China's Qinghai
Province, where so far 21 people have died and scores been injured.
</P>
<P>
Three people are also still reported missing, local officials
said today.
</P>
<P>
Successive rain from June 12 to 16 have triggered floods and
mud flows in 15 counties including two Tibet autonomous
prefectures in Qinghai.
</P>
<P>
Floods have also inundated 2,400 hectares of farmland and
grassland, washed away 12,000 head of domestic animals and damaged
16 highways and 39 bridges and a number of houses and
telecommunications facilities.  
