<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Mayor Calls For Safety Measures after Fatal Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Following a fatal factory blaze
which killed 16 people on Saturday, the mayor of Shenzhen, Li
Zibin, has called for urgent city-wide safety checks in factories
and similar commercial enterprises, hotels and restaurants.
</P>
<P>
He has warned that those failing to meet set safety and hygiene
regulations will be shut down as will all illegal manufacturing
operations. The checks will be particularly stringent at sites
where inflammable items and explosives are stored.
</P>
<P>
A major fire ripped through a four-story building in the Zhimao
Electronics Plant, a Taiwanese-funded firm, which is situated in
Shangxing Village in Shajing Town, Bao'an District of Shenzhen
City at around 17:10 hours on June 12.
</P>
<P>
The conflagration killed 16 people and injured eight others.
The cause of the fire still remains unclear and an investigation
is underway.
</P>
<P>
The incident has aroused concern among Guangdong Provincial
Party and Government officials as well as the Shenzhen City Party
and Government leaders. A special group has been set up to handle
the aftermath of the disaster.
</P>
<P>
Mayor Li has urged the participants to ensure that there is a
responsible and efficient series of safety systems introduced
across the city immediately to prevent further accidents and
fatalities. 
</P>
