<HEADLINE> Cambodian Deminers Move to Assist Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A Mine Action Team from
Cambodia will be sent to Kosovo to help clear mines for the safe
return of Kosovo refugees, according to a press release received
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the Britain-based Mines Advisory Group
(MAG) said that a team of 16 deminers from Kompong Thom, Cambodia
will leave here Saturday for Macedonia en route to Kosovo to help
clear land for the resettlement.
</P>
<P>
The team comprises men and women as well as several amputees
who are working for the MAG which does humanitarian demining in
Cambodia and around the world.
</P>
<P>
"As (Kosovo) refugees are currently spontaneously returning to
their homes now, the need for the Mine Action Team is critical,"
the statement said. 
