<HEADLINE> Mercosur to Establish Association With EU Before 2005 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The South American Common
Market (Mercosur) countries and Bolivia and Chile have decided to
form an "Inter-regional Association" with the European Union (EU)
before the year 2005, a report from Asuncion, capital of Paraguay,
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The decision became official in a declaration signed by heads
of state of Bolivia, Chile and the four Mercosur countries --
Argentina, Brazil, Paraguay and Uruguay -- who attended the 16th
Mercosur summit ending in Asuncion on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Formal talks with the European organization must begin as soon
as possible, and finish before the year 2005, the document urged.
</P>
<P>
The South American heads of state reaffirmed their vow to
continue to strengthen ties with the EU.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the two regional blocs signed a Treaty of Cooperation
to step up relations between them; one year later a similar accord
was reached between Chile and the EU.
</P>
<P>
The Inter-regional Association should be based on rules
established by the World Trade Organization, while taking into
account the viability and need to trade in certain products, and
it should be fortified by a progressively mutual liberalization of
trade, the document said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
