<HEADLINE> Beijing to Hold Auto Show Next Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Beijing International
Automotive Industry Exhibition, also known as Auto China 2000, is
to be held at the China International Exhibition Center in Beijing
June 6-12 next year.
</P>
<P>
Chen Ruowei, president of the China International Exhibition
Center, was quoted by today's China Daily as saying that Auto
China 2000 is expected to cover a record area of 65,000 square
meters.
</P>
<P>
The announcement is made while the country's second largest
auto show is going on in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Auto China 2000 will reflect the great changes that have taken
place in China's auto industry, according to the preparatory
committee.
</P>
<P>
Many domestic enterprises will exhibit high technology
achievements made with the help of foreign investment and
technology transfers, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The show will also feature environment protection and energy
saving. More cars powered by solar energy are expected to appear
on show along with other innovations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
