<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian Foreign Minister Urges KLA to Lay Down Weapons </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini on Wednesday urged the Kosovar Liberation Army (KLA) to lay
down its arms and become a "political force."
</P>
<P>
In a statement to a joint session of the senate and lower house
foreign affairs committees, Dini noted that NATO and the KLA are
currently negotiating such terms and conditions as abstaining from
acts of aggression, turning over heavy weaponry, and giving up
their uniforms.
</P>
<P>
Dini's remarks coincided with renewed appeals and warnings from
other sources regarding the same matter.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday, Prime Minister Massimo D'Alema called on the
Kosovar leaders to cooperate in disarming the KLA, adding that the
reconstruction of peace in the war-ridden Balkans was facing many
difficulties and the international community was required to make
a "very serious commitment."
</P>
<P>
Dini held that the KLA, which has been unwilling to lay down
its arms so far, must be "re-orientated from the logic of armed
confrontation" to one of peaceful cooperation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
