<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Elderly Chinese Man in Coma Regains Consciousness </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- Doctors at a military hospital in
China's Fijian Province brought a 77-year-old man who had been in
coma for more than two and a half years back to consciousness
recently in a rare case.
</P>
<P>
The man went into a coma as a result of an infection, trauma,
and cranial bleeding, according to Lin Pengfei, a doctor in charge
of the case.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Qingming is a retired cadre in Fuzhou who fell down after
a cold bath following a morning run on November 28, 1996. His
family rushed him to a local military hospital where he remained
unconscious for half a year.
</P>
<P>
Doctors used a combination of traditional Chinese medicine and
Western medicine to treat him and his six daughters went to his
bed in turns and talked to him every day.
</P>
<P>
The patient opened his eyes for the first time in May, 1997. a
year later, he could nod and speak and by March of this year, was
able to walk.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
