<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukraine to Boost Ties with Russia, NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine will endeavor to develop
close ties with Russia and the North Atlantic Treaty Organization
(NATO) simultaneously, President Leonid Kuchma said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting with officials from the interior
authorities, Kuchma said that Ukraine and Russia share the same
history and enjoy traditional links in all spheres. Ukraine will
adhere to the stand of always regarding Russia as one of its most
important partners, he declared.
</P>
<P>
The president said both countries should make, as the top
priority, coordinated efforts to raise their economic cooperation
to the corresponding levels. The Ukraine-Russia trade volume
reportedly slumped by about 75 percent at the beginning of this
year in the aftermath of last year's financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of Ukraine's relations with NATO, Kuchma said NATO is
one of the largest and most influential international
organizations in the world today. Ukraine will keep in contact
with NATO within the framework of the Ukraine-NATO Special
Partnership Charter, but is not prepared to join the alliance.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Ukraine-NATO cooperation is not directed
against any other nation. Reaffirming the fact that Ukraine is a
non-aligned nation, Kuchma said it is crucial for Ukraine to
safeguard its national independence, territorial integrity and
national interests. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
