<HEADLINE> Stock Closes Higher in Mexico City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Stock Exchange on
Wednesday closed higher with the benchmark IPC index soaring 328
points, or 6.20 percent, to 5,628.52 points against 5,299.93
points on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 150.86 million shares changed hands for an amount of
around 213.59 million U.S. dollars against 105.52 million shares
worth 115.12 million dollars on the previous day.
</P>
<P>
The local currency, the peso, stood steady at 9.65 to one
dollar for sale and 9.35 for purchase in the main exchange houses
of Mexico City, the same as on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The bullish market was a reflection of a financial program
intended to fortify the economy against the uncertain period ahead,
a chief analyst said.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican Central Bank has received 23.7 billion dollars in
international credits to ward off threats to the peso in 1999-2000,
which will be an election year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
