<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> L.American Consumer Group Warns Against Consumption of Belgian Foods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, June 16 (Xinhua) -- The regional office of the
International Consumers for Latin America and the Caribbean on
Wednesday warned South American consumers not to eat certain kinds
of foods packaged or produced in Belgium.
</P>
<P>
A statement distributed by the Institute of Consumer Rights of
the Lawyers College, "La Plata," said that some Belgian foodstuffs
have been contaminated with dioxin, a toxic substance that could
cause cancer, weaken the body's immune system, alter hormone
production, and possibly cause malformations in embryos.
</P>
<P>
A list of Argentina-imported Belgian foods, which are
considered not suitable for consumption, includes the following
products: chickens, eggs, baby food, frozen poultry, butter,
mayonnaise, and other products that may contain a mixture of eggs
or poultry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
