<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama, EU Sign Economic Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Panama and the European Union
(EU) have signed an agreement on economic cooperation, Panamanian
Foreign Minister Jorge Eduardo Ritter said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement covers a package of projects financed by the EU
and the fund will come in the form of financial and technical
assistance, Ritter said.
</P>
<P>
Around 22 million euros (23.3 million U.S. dollars) will be
invested in the projects, which will benefit small farmers, state
entities undergoing modernization process, production cooperatives
and certain local communities.
</P>
<P>
Santiago Gomez Reino, assistant director of the General
Direction of Foreign Relations of the European Commission was
present at the signing ceremony. 
</P>
</TEXT>
