<HEADLINE> Chinese City Disqualifies Civil Servants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 17 (Xinhua) -- A group of 41 civil servants in
Taiyuan in China's Shanxi Province have recently been dismissed
from their posts for unsatisfactory work performance.
</P>
<P>
The staff members worked in the city's public security
departments, construction design institutes, sanitation offices,
and commercial and industrial bureaus. Some others who did not
pass official exams have been either demoted, penalized, or
transferred.
</P>
<P>
Officials say that all civil servants in over 600 institutions
and more than 50 government departments will take official exams
every year. There were more than 270 who failed this year,
exceeding the total number for the last four years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
