<HEADLINE> Tourism Offers New Jobs in Northeast Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The tourism industry in China's
Liaoning Province has given job possibilities to over 50,000
unemployed workers in the past three years.
</P>
<P>
The number of people in the tourism industry has grown to 320,
000 from a little over 50,000 in the 1980s and tourism has become
an important economic sector.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has given more attention to its
development in the last few years and has pushed for state,
collective, individual, and foreign funds for tourism facilities,
holding a number of travel-related activities, encouraging the
development of accessory industries, and accelerating the use of
tourism resources.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas tourists in the province has increased
17.4 percent annually in the 1990s, and income from tourism by 18.
2 percent annually. The province last year earned 18.4 billion
yuan (2.2 billion U.S. dollars) from tourism, 4.8 percent of its
GDP. 
</P>
</TEXT>
