<HEADLINE> Int'l Fair on Subway, Light Rails, Urban Transport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- The 5th international fair on
subway, light rails and urban transport is scheduled to be held in
Guangzhou, capital of Guangdong Province, from September 21-24
this year.
</P>
<P>
The event is designed to purchase machinery and equipment
needed for the construction of the city's second subway and
another subway in Shenzhen City of the same province.
</P>
<P>
The fair will feature products including subway and light rail
cars, power supply systems, telecommunications and signal systems,
and environmental protection systems. Technical seminars and
product promotion workshops will also be held during the fair.
</P>
<P>
China approved the construction of a second subway in Guangzhou,
a subway in Shenzhen and a third subway in Shanghai last year. And
15 other cities have applied to build their own subways this year.
</P>
<P>
At present, altogether 21 subways as long as 350 kilometers are
being constructed or planned to be built and the total cost is
estimated at 140 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
According to an official in charge of materials supply for the
Guangzhou Subway Company, the first subway of the city was built
mainly with imported equipment and cost 12.7 billion yuan,
averaging 688 million yuan per kilometer.
</P>
<P>
It is learned that local authorities have decided to give
homemade equipment a big share of more than 70 percent in building
the second subway to reduce the cost to 474 million yuan per
kilometer.  
</P>
</TEXT>
