<HEADLINE> Rusedski Edges Jan-Michael Gambill in Nottingham Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Greg Rusedski of Britain edged Jan-
Michael Gambill 4-6, 6-4, 7-5 to move into the quarter-finals of
the Nottingham open tennis tournament on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The British number two, one of the favourites for the Wimbledon
title this year, displayed problems with his return of serve and
often erratic backhand. When the frustration got the better of him,
he threw his racket to the ground on a couple of occasions.
</P>
<P>
Gambill, the American ranked 50 in the world, broke Rusesdki in
the ninth game of the first set and also held a break point again
midway through the second after Rusedski double-faulted three
times in succession.
</P>
<P>
But Rusedski hauled himself out of trouble and victory was
clinched when Gambill made one mistake too many on his own serve.
</P>
<P>
Rusedski now meets 18-year-old Australian Lleyton Hewitt, who
eased past Guillermo Canas of Argentina 6-2, 7-5.
</P>
<P>
Number two seed Jerome Golmard of France withdrew from the
tournament with a knee injury as a precaution with Wimbledon only
five days away. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
