<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0030 GMT, June 17 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Wednesday reaffirmed its sovereignty over the
three islands in the Persian Gulf in a response to the call of the
United Arab Emirates (UAE) for a peaceful solution to their
dispute over the islands.
</P>
<P>
"The legal status of the three Iranian islands, Abu Musa, the
Greater and Lesser Tunbs are clearly transparent and there exist
no legal ambiguity in this regard," Iranian Majlis (parliament)
Vice Speaker Hassan Rowhani said. (Iran-UAE)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- NATO and the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) have
reached agreement on an outline plan for disarming KLA fighters,
according to British government sources.
</P>
<P>
They said on Wednesday that the framework agreement had been
forwarded to the North Atlantic Council, NATO's ruling political
body. Details were still being discussed, a Reuters report said. (
NATO-Kosovo)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- U.N. Security Council on Wednesday called on
all parties to take the necessary steps to allow the ballot for
East Timor's future to go peacefully.
</P>
<P>
Following consultations, the council issued a press statement
by June president, Gambia's Baboucarr-Blaise Ismaila Jagne, saying
that it would like to see the electoral process to be in "an
atmosphere free of intimidation and violence from all quarters". (
UN-East Timor)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- Romania's President Emil Constantinescu Wednesday
appealed for a durable stability of the entire south-eastern
European zone.
</P>
<P>
Holding a joint press conference with his visiting Greek
counterpart Constantinos Stephanopoulos, the Romanian head of
state stressed the necessity for urgently enforcing the procedures
of the pact of stability for south-eastern Europe. (Romania-Greece)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- A senior Russian diplomat said here Wednesday
that the 15-nation U.N. Security Council needed to deal with the
refusal of the rebel Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) to disarm, an
obvious violation of a key U.N. resolution on the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Sergey Lavrov, Russian permanent representative to the United
Nations, told reporters after a closed-door Security Council
meeting that NATO troops stood by as KLA guerrillas moved into
positions, contrary to an omnibus resolution approving a Kosovo
peace plan last week. (Russia-KLA) 
</P>
