<HEADLINE> German-Funded Automotive Technology Company Operational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SUZHOU, June 17 (Xinhua) -- An automotive technology company
funded by the German driving gear developer and manufacturer ZF
Friedrichshafen AG, has gone operational in the Suzhou Industrial
Park in Jiangsu Province, east China.
</P>
<P>
The company, ZF Drivetech (Suzhou) Co., Ltd., will produce
manual gearboxes, front and rear axles, and parts below the
chassis for big passenger buses at its first stage.
</P>
<P>
The ZF group, nearly 100 years old, invested some 10 million
German marks in the first phase of the Suzhou venture.  
</P>
