<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Peru Bans Meat Import From Belgium </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, June 16 (Xinhua) -- Peru on Wednesday suspended imports
of poultry, pork, beef and all meal products, as well as all types
of sausages and milk of Belgian origin, for a 90 day period in
order to prevent dioxin contamination.
</P>
<P>
A resolution from the National Service of Agricultural
Sanitation (SENASA) said on Wednesday that as the cancer-causing
dioxin had been evidently found in the aforementioned products
coming from Belgium, it was necessary to impose an import ban on
them to safeguard the nation.
</P>
<P>
During the restrictive period, SENASA will conduct evaluation
studies on the possible risks, to decide whether the restriction
should be lifted or extended at the end of the 90 days.
</P>
<P>
Peru prohibited imports of powdered milk from Belgium on June
11, after reports of dioxin contamination, a highly carcinogenic
chemical. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990617.0336 </DOCNO>
