<HEADLINE> Greene Breaks Men's 100 Meters World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 16 (Xinhua) -- World champion Maurice Greene of
the United States broke the 100 meters world record by clocking 9.
79 seconds at an international athletics meeting here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The American shaved 0.05 seconds off the previous record of 9.
84 seconds set by Donovan Bailey of Canada at the Olympic Games in
1996.
</P>
<P>
Trinidad's Ato Boldon finished second in 9.86 while third
placer was Bruny Surin of Canada in 9.97.
</P>
<P>
Greene won the world championships 100 meters race on the same
track in 1997, clocking 9.86 then. 
</P>
